            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Hi everyone\nI have taken admission for my son in Grade 3 this academic year. He is very happy and doing well. If we want to complete any task the most important part is planning and after that execution. School planning and updating the parents in advance is the best part of the school .Even though my son is in 3rd Grade I am aware of higher standards updates also. I agree with them that the teaching pattern and schedule is different from the primary classes. School has a different format for higher classes than the primary ones. Every child is different. Some children are grasping in one go but many are there they require revisions. Schools are taking multiple revisions  for higher classes. I hope the same pattern will follow in future . Rest teachers admins and other supporting staff are very cooperative. Here I am mentioning one sentence which was said by them in one PTM.\nSTRESS FREE  EXAMS AND\nCHILDREN'S SHOULD ENJOY THE EXAMS.\nThank you",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
